sentences: Kenza Farah (born 8 July 1986) is a Franco-Algerian singer-songwriter.
Her album Authentik won gold in its second week.
Kenza Farah was born on 8 July 1986 in Béjaïa, Algeria and grew up in the 15th arrondissement of Marseille.
Followed by a singing competition, Farah met the producers who allowed her to record some songs in the studio, including "Mon Ange", "Trésor" and "Il ma trahie".
